ata-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_8420942\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 29, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104lbc1665702906688.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lbc1665702906688.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lbc1665702906688.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"lbc1665702906688\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                                 \n Create a Root CA Certificate\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Create a root certificate that can be used to generate intermediate certificates.\n </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lbc1665702906688__li_d19937e1_d19938e1_d19939e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"lbc1665702906688__p_d39686e1_d39687e1_d39688e1\">Create or edit an OpenSSL configuration file\n               called <span class=\"ph filepath\">ca_root.cnf</span> for the creation of the CA root certificate. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">You can download a sample <span class=\"ph filepath\">ca_root.cnf</span>file from a number of\n               web sites. You will have to adapt it to your situation, specifically the names and\n               locations of your key and certificate in the [CA_default] section.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lbc1665702906688__li_d19940e1_d19941e1_d19942e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"lbc1665702906688__p_d39689e1_d39690e1_d39691e1\">Generate the key using a strong encryption algorithm, such as 4096-bit AES256. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pxj1665702548359.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pxj1665702548359.html\" title=\"A private key is required for encrypting the certificate used in authenticating the peers in TLS -secured communication. It is also used for data encryption, typically to encrypt the exchange of symmetric keys that are used for the duration of the TLS session.\">Generate a Private Key for Use with Certificates</a>.\n                                    For example:</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">openssl genrsa -aes256 -out ca_root.key 4096</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lbc1665702906688__p_d39692e1_d39693e1_d39694e1\">When prompted for a pass phrase, use a strong one.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"lbc1665702906688__note_w5101ab1b5b1b3b3b5_w5102ab1b5b1b3b3_w5103ab1b5b1b3_w5104ab1b5b1_w5105ab1b5_w5106ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Keep this key secure! If it is compromised, malicious users can make fake certificates that are not distinguishable from real ones.</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lbc1665702906688__li_d19943e1_d19944e1_d19945e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"lbc1665702906688__p_d39695e1_d39696e1_d39697e1\">Create the root CA certificate that is valid for\n               a significant amount of time, such as 20 years. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">openssl req -config ca_root.cnf /\n -key ca_root.key /\n -new -x509 -days 7305 -sha256 -extensions v3_ca /\n -out ca_root.crt\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">By definition, a CA root certificate is trusted, so there is no need to create a\n               signing request.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lbc1665702906688__li_d19946e1_d19947e1_d19948e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Verify the root CA certificate:\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">openssl x509 -noout -text -in ca_root.crt</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"lbc1665702906688__result_w5098ab1b5b3_w5099ab1b5_w5100ab1\">\n<div class=\"sectiondiv postreq\" id=\"lbc1665702906688__topic_d39698e1_d39699e1_d39700e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lbc1665702906688__p_d39701e1_d39702e1_d39703e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hso1665702906774.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hso1665702906774.html\" title=\"You can create intermediate certificates using a root certificate.\">Create Intermediate CA Certificates</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8420942\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8420942\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Create a Root CA Certificate Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 29, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Create a Root CA Certificate Create a root certificate that can be used to generate intermediate certificates. Create or edit an OpenSSL configuration file called ca_root.cnf for the creation of the CA root certificate. You can download a sample ca_root.cnf file from a number of web sites. You will have to adapt it to your situation, specifically the names and locations of your key and certificate in the [CA_default] section. Generate the key using a strong encryption algorithm, such as 4096-bit AES256. For more information, see Generate a Private Key for Use with Certificates . For example: openssl genrsa -aes256 -out ca_root.key 4096 Copy When prompted for a pass phrase, use a strong one. Note: Keep this key secure! If it is compromised, malicious users can make fake certificates that are not distinguishable from real ones. Create the root CA certificate that is valid for a significant amount of time, such as 20 years. openssl req -config ca_root.cnf / -key ca_root.key / -new -x509 -days 7305 -sha256 -extensions v3_ca / -out ca_root.crt Copy By definition, a CA root certificate is trusted, so there is no need to create a signing request. Verify the root CA certificate: openssl x509 -noout -text -in ca_root.crt Copy For more information, see Create Intermediate CA Certificates . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}